00:31:16.900 --> 00:31:20.000
modified foods in detail
here, but this is a

00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:22.230
very emotive subject.

00:31:22.230 --> 00:31:25.230
Basically speaking, there is
what I call the "agromantic"

00:31:25.230 --> 00:31:28.000
side of plant breeding where
it's all very lovely, and

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:31.280
going out, and mixing with the
birds and bees, and so forth.

00:31:31.280 --> 00:31:33.680
But this is worth reading
because this guy won the Nobel

00:31:33.680 --> 00:31:34.410
Prize for this.

00:31:34.410 --> 00:31:38.710
He was working with
Drosophila moths.

00:31:38.710 --> 00:31:41.170
Basically speaking,
he used x-ray

00:31:41.170 --> 00:31:44.860
radiation to zap the flies.

00:31:44.860 --> 00:31:48.550
What it does is rattle their
genome to bits, and then it'll

00:31:48.550 --> 00:31:52.280
all fall back together again,
causing mutations.

00:31:52.280 --> 00:31:56.680
He was able to speed up breeding
of these flies by

00:31:56.680 --> 00:32:00.180
tens of years because he could
play around with the genome in

00:32:00.180 --> 00:32:01.900
a way that you couldn't do it.

00:32:01.900 --> 00:32:05.900
So that was extended
to plants then.

00:32:05.900 --> 00:32:09.540
Although this is in Japan, it's
no longer used, because

00:32:09.540 --> 00:32:11.380
there are much smaller
versions of it now.

00:32:11.380 --> 00:32:14.470
But basically speaking, what
happens is the plant is hit

00:32:14.470 --> 00:32:17.520
with atomic radiation.

00:32:17.520 --> 00:32:18.610
And it goes something
like this.

00:32:18.610 --> 00:32:20.400
The radiation hits the
genome of the plant.

00:32:20.400 --> 00:32:25.090
There's the healthy plants in
a circle around the genome.

00:32:25.090 --> 00:32:28.000
Then the genome was wrecked.

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:29.870
The vast majority of
plants are useless.

00:32:29.870 --> 00:32:32.760
But the one in the circle, the
one in the circle has some

00:32:32.760 --> 00:32:34.620
trait that's good.

00:32:34.620 --> 00:32:40.010
And they back breed that with
the original plant and hope to

00:32:40.010 --> 00:32:41.450
achieve something.

00:32:41.450 --> 00:32:43.760
And this is promoted by
the United Nations.

00:32:43.760 --> 00:32:45.980
To speed through this,
examples--

00:32:45.980 --> 00:32:48.550
all the rice you eat in the
United States is grown by

00:32:48.550 --> 00:32:51.050
atomic radiation.

00:32:51.050 --> 00:32:53.175
All the grapefruits you eat in
the United States is grown by

00:32:53.175 --> 00:32:54.590
the radiation.

00:32:54.590 --> 00:32:57.140
All the whiskey you drink in
Scotland and Ireland comes

00:32:57.140 --> 00:32:58.590
from barley that was mutated.

00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:03.990
The figure is about 200,000
varieties have been released

00:33:03.990 --> 00:33:06.940
by the United Nations using
this technology.

00:33:06.940 --> 00:33:09.340
If you compare that
to GM technology,

00:33:09.340 --> 00:33:11.530
it is cut and paste.

00:33:11.530 --> 00:33:14.320
So here you have, in the blue,
you've got a gene.

00:33:14.320 --> 00:33:15.920
You've got an enzyme
that splices the

00:33:15.920 --> 00:33:18.170
precise gene you want.

00:33:18.170 --> 00:33:23.300
It then goes over the red gene
and the enzyme takes a part of

00:33:23.300 --> 00:33:25.800
that out, puts the gene
in at another end, and

00:33:25.800 --> 00:33:26.950
stitches it up again.

00:33:26.950 --> 00:33:29.450
Highly, highly precision.

00:33:29.450 --> 00:33:33.910
If you make a comparison between
trying to get the same

00:33:33.910 --> 00:33:38.080
trait in a plant using atomic
radiation versus genetic

00:33:38.080 --> 00:33:43.020
engineering, you find that you
have about 30 genes with

00:33:43.020 --> 00:33:46.030
changed expression in genetic
engineering compared to 1,000

00:33:46.030 --> 00:33:50.440
genes changed in atomic
mutation.

00:33:50.440 --> 00:33:52.410
You can sell the atomic mutated

00:33:52.410 --> 00:33:54.930
plants at your leisure.

00:33:54.930 --> 00:33:55.590
No rules.

00:33:55.590 --> 00:33:56.470
No regulations.

00:33:56.470 --> 00:33:57.700
No nothing.

00:33:57.700 --> 00:34:00.660
You cannot sell the GM crops.

00:34:03.870 --> 00:34:08.130
Coming to the end of my talk
now, just to say that there

00:34:08.130 --> 00:34:13.719
