00:55:44.005 --> 00:55:46.130
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:55:46.130 --> 00:55:49.680
Just interesting to hear your
thoughts around nutrition

00:55:49.680 --> 00:55:51.800
during pregnancy and how
that primes people

00:55:51.800 --> 00:55:52.910
for later in life.

00:55:52.910 --> 00:55:55.630
I was lucky enough to get your
free copy of your book.

00:55:55.630 --> 00:55:57.310
I'm just reading the back,
and I couldn't wait

00:55:57.310 --> 00:55:58.960
to hear that bit.

00:55:58.960 --> 00:56:01.850
PROFESSOR MIKE GIBNEY: Well,
it is interesting.

00:56:01.850 --> 00:56:04.220
Basically speaking, you inherit
your genes from your

00:56:04.220 --> 00:56:05.800
mother and your father.

00:56:05.800 --> 00:56:13.900
And they sit into the embryo,
and they nurse along.

00:56:13.900 --> 00:56:17.260
And the genes are--

00:56:17.260 --> 00:56:19.000
well, let me go back
a little bit.

00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:24.130
In my right earlobe, I have
my entire genome.

00:56:24.130 --> 00:56:27.350
And in my liver, I have
my entire genome.

00:56:27.350 --> 00:56:30.380
But my liver doesn't hear
anything, and my earlobe

00:56:30.380 --> 00:56:32.172
doesn't make anything.

00:56:32.172 --> 00:56:35.660
The reason why they differ is
the things that the liver does

00:56:35.660 --> 00:56:37.490
are switched off
in the earlobe.

00:56:37.490 --> 00:56:39.310
And the things that the earlobe
does are switched off

00:56:39.310 --> 00:56:40.270
in the liver.

00:56:40.270 --> 00:56:41.790
So genes are switched
up, or switched

00:56:41.790 --> 00:56:43.432
down, or switched off.

00:56:43.432 --> 00:56:51.360
Now in pregnancy, the mother's
environment has a big say in

00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:53.920
how the dimmer switch
is operated, whether

00:56:53.920 --> 00:56:56.240
it goes up or down.

00:56:56.240 --> 00:56:58.870
When the child is born then,
if they're born into an

00:56:58.870 --> 00:57:02.870
environment that matches the
plan that the mother had for

00:57:02.870 --> 00:57:04.365
them, they're fine.

00:57:04.365 --> 00:57:08.550
If they don't, by the time they
get to 50 or 60, they

00:57:08.550 --> 00:57:12.220
will begin to develop chronic
disease at a great rate.

00:57:12.220 --> 00:57:15.940
So there's fabulous stuff which
goes back to, say the

00:57:15.940 --> 00:57:19.040
Dutch famine during the Second
World War, where people

00:57:19.040 --> 00:57:23.180
entered that famine pregnant,
got pregnant during it, or had

00:57:23.180 --> 00:57:25.145
a baby during it, so [INAUDIBLE]
different

00:57:25.145 --> 00:57:26.690
trimesters of pregnancy.

00:57:26.690 --> 00:57:30.060
And looking at those people,
those survivors, 40, 50 years

00:57:30.060 --> 00:57:34.220
later, you can see the point in
pregnancy where the damage

00:57:34.220 --> 00:57:39.210
is done, where their genes were
altered in such a way to

00:57:39.210 --> 00:57:41.350
expect a very, very low
level of food in

00:57:41.350 --> 00:57:42.760
Holland at the time.

00:57:42.760 --> 00:57:45.630
And they grow up into this
obesogenic environment, and

00:57:45.630 --> 00:57:46.620
it's a mismatch.

00:57:46.620 --> 00:57:54.220
A very hot topic, and I'll go
further than that to say that

00:57:54.220 --> 00:57:57.320
in the period immediately
after birth--

00:57:57.320 --> 00:58:01.810
the example I was always take
is, let's say, my grandson.

00:58:01.810 --> 00:58:03.200
He's going to learn English.

00:58:03.200 --> 00:58:05.410
He's going to learn to eat
with a knife and fork.

00:58:05.410 --> 00:58:08.045
He's going to learn all the
cultural things we do.

00:58:08.045 --> 00:58:10.790
A child born yesterday in
Taiwan is going to do

00:58:10.790 --> 00:58:12.350
something completely
different.

00:58:12.350 --> 00:58:16.520
So the humans are born with
a non-hardwired brain.

00:58:16.520 --> 00:58:18.496
Our brain is plastic.

00:58:18.496 --> 00:58:21.170
A colt is born with
a hardwired brain.

00:58:21.170 --> 00:58:22.900
It gets up on its four
legs, and it trots

00:58:22.900 --> 00:58:24.420
off with its mummy.

00:58:24.420 --> 00:58:25.770
[INAUDIBLE]

00:58:25.770 --> 00:58:26.630
has nothing to learn.

00:58:26.630 --> 00:58:28.570
You can teach it a few tricks.

00:58:28.570 --> 00:58:31.910
But humans have to have that
plastic brain in order to

00:58:31.910 --> 00:58:33.780
absorb all the culture
they are born into.

00:58:37.100 --> 00:58:39.400
What's referred to now,
particularly in the developing

00:58:39.400 --> 00:58:41.390
world, is the first
1,000 days.

00:58:41.390 --> 00:58:44.190
That covers conception right
through to two years of age.

00:58:44.190 --> 00:58:48.240
If you get nutrition wrong
there, you have trouble in

00:58:48.240 --> 00:58:49.620
later life.

00:58:49.620 --> 00:58:50.660
And it's irreversible.

00:58:50.660 --> 00:58:54.790
So for example, if you don't get
proper brain development

00:58:54.790 --> 00:58:56.630
in that two-year period, because
the brain is still

00:58:56.630 --> 00:59:01.200
growing, it will be
irreversible.

00:59:01.200 --> 00:59:03.960
You'll have a low IQ
all your life.

00:59:03.960 --> 00:59:07.090
If you don't get enough food to
build the body in those two

00:59:07.090 --> 00:59:09.880
years, it will set your
height much lower than

00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:10.760
your genetic potential.

00:59:10.760 --> 00:59:12.810
So you'll be physically stunted,
and you won't have

00:59:12.810 --> 00:59:15.380
the physical capacity
to do work.

00:59:15.380 --> 00:59:20.050
So there's a recognition now,
a huge recognition that is

00:59:20.050 --> 00:59:22.130
important, and the United
Nations have this protocol

00:59:22.130 --> 00:59:23.810
scaling up nutrition.

00:59:23.810 --> 00:59:25.730
And they focus on this
first 1,000 days.

00:59:25.730 --> 00:59:29.140
Hillary Clinton is one of the
big champions of this, and our

00:59:29.140 --> 00:59:31.630
own minister [INAUDIBLE].

00:59:31.630 --> 00:59:33.370
It's a really absorbing area.

00:59:33.370 --> 00:59:35.245
It's fascinating.

